Epic: Implement Cluster Observability Solution
We are implementing a cluster observability solution to monitor system-level and Kubernetes-level metrics across OpenShift clusters. A proof of concept (PoC) has already been completed — Ansible code is available and deploys observability components into a separate namespace.

The solution includes:

Deploying node-exporters to gather system-level metrics.

Deploying kube-state-metrics.

Sending metrics to a remote write endpoint.

All deployments should be fully automated using Ansible and maintained in GitHub with proper README documentation.

Subtasks / Issues to Create
Deploy observability components in a separate namespace

Use Ansible to deploy node-exporters and kube-state-metrics on target OpenShift clusters.

Deploy to 10% of clusters (6 clusters) with varying worker node counts for validation.

Enable user-workload monitoring.

Configure and validate remote write setup.

Configure authentication

Set up authentication for both the managed clusters and the remote write receiver.

Deploy remote write receiver with NFS-backed storage

Deploy the receiver on a cluster using NFS server as the data storage backend.

Set up monitoring on this receiver to collect storage usage metrics.

Analyze storage usage over time to evaluate the need for a long-term solution (e.g., Thanos) for historical data retention.

Configure Grafana access and dashboards

